<h2>Report an issue</h2>

<p>Issues are problems that are currently affecting your project. To report an issue:</p>

<ol>
    <li>Go to the project details page</li>
    <li>Click on the <strong>Issues</strong> tab</li>
    <li>Click the <strong>Add issue</strong> button</li>
    <li>Fill in the issue details:
        <ul>
            <li>Title (required) - A brief description of the issue</li>
            <li>Description (required) - Detailed explanation of the issue</li>
            <li>Severity (required) - low, medium, high, or critical</li>
            <li>Status (required) - open, in progress, blocked, resolved, or closed</li>
            <li>Resolution (optional) - How the issue was or will be resolved</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Click <strong>Create</strong> to save the issue</li>
</ol>

<h3>Tips</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Report issues as soon as they are identified</li>
    <li>Use appropriate severity levels to help prioritise work</li>
    <li>Update the status as you work through resolving the issue</li>
    <li>Document the resolution for future reference</li>
    <li>Close issues once they are fully resolved</li>
</ul>

<p>Issues differ from risks in that they are current problems, whereas risks are potential future problems.</p>

